## Description

With the addition of collection literals in .NET 8, analyzer suggestion `IDE0305` has been introduced. This suggestion appears on code such as this;
```cs
int[] M(List<int> foo) => foo.ToArray(); // Collection initialization can be simplified
```
The suggested change is the following;
```cs
int[] M(List<int> foo) => [.. foo];
```

## Issue

The new syntax is certainly very nice, but actually leads to non-trivial performance regressions (up to 4x worse). You can find some benchmarking results below. I completely understand the desire for this suggestion, but find it questionable when it doesn't actually offer an equivalent outcome. Especially with all the performance-related analyzer suggestions that .NET 8 added elsewhere.

## Benchmark

```cs
